You are executing the /catchup skill for the Builds workspace.

## Purpose
Start every session with a 60-second briefing. Runs in an isolated sub-agent so that
SSH output, log data, and JSON state never pollute the main context window.
Only the final briefing enters the main session.

---

## Your job as the main agent

Do NOT run any SSH commands or read any files yourself. Instead:

1. Use the **Agent tool** (subagent_type="general") with the task prompt below.

2. When the sub-agent returns, output its briefing verbatim to the user.

3. If the briefing shows a service as DOWN or contains ERROR/CRITICAL lines,
   call those out explicitly and ask if the user wants to investigate before working.

---

## Sub-agent task prompt (pass this to the Agent tool)

You are gathering a session briefing for a developer. Collect data from the sources
below, then produce a single compact summary. Do not show raw data — only the report.

## Step 1 - Read memory files

Read both files in full:
- C:\\Users\\benja\\.claude\\projects\\c--Users-benja-OneDrive-Documents-Builds\\memory\\MEMORY.md
- C:\\Users\\benja\\.claude\\projects\\c--Users-benja-OneDrive-Documents-Builds\\memory\\rapid2.md

Note any known issues or pending items from rapid2.md.

## Step 2 - Check EC2 service health

Run:
  ssh rapid2 "sudo systemctl is-active openclaw-paper.service && sudo journalctl -u openclaw-paper.service --no-pager -n 30 | grep -E 'ERROR|CRITICAL|WARNING|BUY|SELL|S3|Started|Stopped'"

Note: Rapid2 v1 (3.131.96.193) is retired as of 2026-03-04 - do not check it.

## Step 3 - Read portfolio state

Run:
  ssh rapid2 "cat /home/ubuntu/rapid2-v1.2/state/paper_state.json"

From the JSON, extract:
- paper_usd (cash on hand)
- starting_value
- number of open positions and their symbols grouped by tier
- Approximate total value at entry prices (sum position qty * entry_price + cash)

## Step 4 - Check for recent decisions

Run:
  ssh rapid2 "find /home/ubuntu/rapid2-v1.2/docs/decisions -name '*.md' 2>/dev/null | sort | tail -5"

Also check locally: c:/Users/benja/OneDrive/Documents/Builds/Rapid2/rapid2 v1.2/docs/decisions/

## Step 5 - Git status

Run in the v1.2 directory (use cd then commands, or full path):
  cd "c:/Users/benja/OneDrive/Documents/Builds/Rapid2/rapid2 v1.2" && git log --oneline -3 && git status --short

## Step 6 - Produce the briefing

Return ONLY the report below. No preamble. No raw data. Just the formatted briefing.

If any service is DOWN or errors were found, put those at the very top as a warning
before the normal report structure.

--- SESSION CATCHUP ---
Date: [today's date]

SERVICES
  Paper bot: [active / inactive]

PORTFOLIO
  Cash:      $[paper_usd]
  Positions: [count] open
    T2: [symbols]
    T3: [symbols]
  Value:     ~$[total at entry] vs $[starting_value] starting ([+/-X%])

RECENT ACTIVITY (last 30 log lines)
  Trades:  [BUY/SELL lines, or "none"]
  Errors:  [ERROR/CRITICAL lines, or "none"]
  Other:   [notable WARNINGs, or omit]

GIT (v1.2)
  Last commit: [message]
  Uncommitted: [files, or "clean"]

OPEN DECISIONS
  [ADR files found, or "none recorded"]

KNOWN ISSUES
  [from rapid2.md Known Issues section — bullet list]

---
